other_tests.findings: There is bibasilar atelectasis. There is a 1.4 cm metallic density structure at the right lung base, possibly a retained bullet fragment. There is a region of peripheral hyperenhancement in hepatic segment 6 measuring 3.2 x 2.1 cm, most likely a transient hepatic attenuation difference. The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated, measuring up to 9 mm in diameter, with wall hyperenhancement.
